{{Infobox institute |name = Australasian Society for Continental Philosophy |image = |image_size = |image_alt = |caption = |latin_name = |motto = |founder = Graham Jones, Paul Atkinson, Ralph Humphries, Andrew Johnson, Clive Madder, Michael Fagenblatt, Simon Cooper, Melissa McMahon |established = 1995 |mission = |focus = |president = [[Richard Colledge]] |chairman = |head_label = |head = |faculty = |adjunct_faculty = |staff = |key_people = [[Joanne Faulkner]] |budget = |endowment = |debt = |num_members = |subsidiaries = |owner = |non-profit_slogan = |former_name = |location = |coor = |address = |website = [https://www.ascp.org.au/ www.ascp.org.au] |footnotes = }}
'''Australasian Society for Continental Philosophy''' ('''ASCP''') is a society dedicated to providing a broad intellectual forum for the scholars researching in [[continental philosophy]].<ref>[https://hal.arts.unsw.edu.au/ascp2015/ ASCP Conference 2-4 December 2015]</ref><ref>[https://books.publishing.monash.edu/apps/bookworm/view/A+Companion+to+Philosophy+in+Australia+and+New+Zealand/56/xhtml/chapter01a.html A Companion to Philosophy in Australia and New Zealand] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303214544/https://books.publishing.monash.edu/apps/bookworm/view/A%2BCompanion%2Bto%2BPhilosophy%2Bin%2BAustralia%2Band%2BNew%2BZealand/56/xhtml/chapter01a.html |date=March 3, 2016 }}</ref> The society was established in [[Melbourne]] in 1995. [[Richard Colledge]] is the chair and [[Joanne Faulkner]] is the deputy-chair of the society. The Society is the successor of the defunct Australian Association of Phenomenology and Social Philosophy (AAPSP)<ref>[https://www.ascp.org.au/about-the-ascp/history-of-the-ascp History of the ASCP]</ref>
